The paper deals with joint source-channel coding for a block-fading MIMO channel, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and multiple-input multiple-output (cs.MM) sub-categories. The proposed digital layered transmission scheme involves time layering and superposition, which are common techniques in signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different transmission schemes, which could be relevant to communication theory (cs.COM).
